A discription of Tangier, the country and people adjoyning with an account of the person and government of Gayland, the present usurper of the kingdome of Fez, and a short narrative of the proceedings of the English in those parts : whereunto is added, the copy of a letter from the King of Fez to the King of England, for assistance against his rebellious subjects, and another from Grayland to His Sacred Majesty Charles the Second : with divers letters and passages worthy of note / translated from the Spanish into English, and published by authority. Charles I, King of England, 1600-1649. Charles II, King of England, 1630-1685. Ghaylān, Aḥmad al-Khāḍir ibn ʻAlī, d. 1673. Teviot, Andrew Rutherford, Earl of, d. 1664.
[6], 84 p. : port.
Printed for Samuel Speed ..., London : 1664.
Reproduction of original in Huntington Library.
